modules.description: Provides serialization and deserialization between a connection structure and S-expressions, along with equality checks. Works with a custom type representing connection parameters, including host, port, and authentication details. Parses connection strings into this type and returns a default instance for initialization.

Handles blob storage operations including uploading, downloading, and listing blobs using Azure's REST API. Works with byte arrays, blob metadata, and container names to interact with cloud storage. Enables efficient data transfer and management for cloud-based applications.

Encodes and decodes connection parameters using S-expressions, supporting host, port, and authentication fields. Enables parsing of connection strings into structured values and generates default configurations. Equality checks ensure consistent comparison of connection settings. Examples include converting a connection string to a parameter record and verifying if two configurations match.
